procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), pregnancy testing, and screening for HIV, hepatitis B and C.

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour pooled collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content. Date, time, and weight of each sample are recorded.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A complete physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Height, weight, and BMI are also measured.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Study Drug Administration
procedures.label: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets (15 mg or 30 mg) with 240 mL of water.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches to analyze for copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE/SAE Monitoring
procedures.description: Detection, collection, and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs) throughout the study.

procedures.name: Urinalysis
procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of urine for clinical assessment.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatments.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws. A catheter may not be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms for cardiac safety monitoring.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
